WEBVTT

00:00:11.116 --> 00:00:15.078
NOTES FROM THE LAST ROW

00:00:54.868 --> 00:00:55.702
<i>Lee Min-yeong.</i>

00:00:56.286 --> 00:00:57.120
Here.

00:00:58.204 --> 00:00:59.455
Jang Han-seul.

00:01:00.832 --> 00:01:01.749
Jang Han-seul?

00:01:02.667 --> 00:01:03.710
Jang Han-seul.

00:01:07.714 --> 00:01:08.631
Heo Do-jun.

00:01:08.715 --> 00:01:09.591
Here.

00:01:13.845 --> 00:01:17.223
I reviewed your last assignments
and left them over there.

00:01:17.307 --> 00:01:19.475
Make sure to collect them after class.

00:01:19.559 --> 00:01:20.602
Yes, Professor.

00:01:21.728 --> 00:01:22.854
Did you take notes?

00:01:24.522 --> 00:01:27.567
-Can you lend them to me next time?
-I'll send them to you.

00:01:32.697 --> 00:01:34.824
Professor!

00:01:37.744 --> 00:01:39.245
This…

00:01:40.496 --> 00:01:43.958
I mean, "trash"?
How could you write something like this?

00:01:44.042 --> 00:01:45.960
You should know, sir,

00:01:46.461 --> 00:01:48.463
that I'm an influencer.

00:01:49.422 --> 00:01:51.799
Do you even know what that means?

00:01:52.842 --> 00:01:55.887
My blog alone has over 30,000 subscribers.

00:01:56.596 --> 00:01:58.389
Do you know how many likes I get a day?

00:01:58.890 --> 00:01:59.766
Is that right?

00:02:00.642 --> 00:02:02.185
How impressive.

00:02:02.727 --> 00:02:04.520
Then that blog must be a trash can.

00:02:04.604 --> 00:02:05.563
On second thought,

00:02:05.647 --> 00:02:08.775
if it's full of writing like this,
a "landfill" might be more fitting.

00:02:12.737 --> 00:02:14.280
Twelve paragraphs

00:02:14.864 --> 00:02:17.116
and 167 sentences.

00:02:17.617 --> 00:02:20.787
You may consider this writing
since you filled the pages with whatever,

00:02:21.287 --> 00:02:24.624
but unfortunately, these pages
don't hold a single true sentence.

00:02:25.375 --> 00:02:28.628
Not a single sentence
that comes from the heart and rings true.

00:02:29.587 --> 00:02:32.507
It's just a plethora of clichés,
cheap sentimentality,

00:02:32.590 --> 00:02:36.010
and sentences copied and pasted
from other people's work.

00:02:36.886 --> 00:02:38.721
How else should I describe these words

00:02:38.805 --> 00:02:41.849
you've simply regurgitated
without grasping their meaning?

00:02:42.600 --> 00:02:45.687
If you can think of a more fitting term
than "trash," let me know.

00:02:48.398 --> 00:02:51.109
Then, going forward,
I'll try to use that word.

00:02:57.824 --> 00:02:59.033
Are we done here?

00:03:04.414 --> 00:03:05.331
What an asshole.

00:03:05.832 --> 00:03:09.377
I could just strangle him.
That soul-crushing bastard.

00:03:09.460 --> 00:03:11.337
If only his class was optional.

00:03:13.006 --> 00:03:15.466
I heard he acts like that
because he's insecure.

00:03:17.593 --> 00:03:19.762
<i>Our seniors told me over drinks one time.</i>

00:03:20.430 --> 00:03:22.432
<i>Heo Mun-oh has only written one novel.</i>

00:03:22.932 --> 00:03:24.600
<i>Over 20 years ago, at that.</i>

00:03:25.101 --> 00:03:28.146
<i>But he hasn't been able to write</i>
<i>a second novel since.</i>

00:03:28.646 --> 00:03:31.482
<i>He wants to, but he can't,</i>
<i>no matter how hard he fucking tries.</i>

00:03:31.566 --> 00:03:35.695
<i>So he takes his inferiority complex</i>
<i>and stress out on his students.</i>

00:03:36.404 --> 00:03:37.488
<i>Total loser.</i>

00:03:38.072 --> 00:03:39.615
RESEARCH IN PROGRESS
DO NOT DISTURB

00:03:40.950 --> 00:03:41.868
Mun-oh, you're here.

00:03:43.494 --> 00:03:45.038
The door was unlocked, so…

00:03:48.416 --> 00:03:51.169
Professor Park,
didn't we see each other yesterday?

00:03:51.252 --> 00:03:54.630
Well, that was yesterday, Mun-oh.
I came because I wanted to see you <i>today</i>.

00:03:54.714 --> 00:03:57.759
Calling me Mun-oh again.
I told you to stop using my name.

00:03:57.842 --> 00:03:59.135
Yes, Professor Heo.

00:04:00.219 --> 00:04:02.889
But I like calling you by name.

00:04:03.806 --> 00:04:05.516
Did you get home safe yesterday?

00:04:05.600 --> 00:04:08.519
-Want some coffee?
-No, I just had some.

00:04:09.228 --> 00:04:11.439
Goodness, what is this?

00:04:11.522 --> 00:04:13.024
You're so stubborn, Mun-oh.

00:04:13.107 --> 00:04:15.943
Do you still take attendance by hand?

00:04:16.944 --> 00:04:19.697
Shall I install the software for you?
It's so much easier.

00:04:19.781 --> 00:04:21.366
No, thank you.

00:04:21.449 --> 00:04:23.284
I like doing things my way.

00:04:24.118 --> 00:04:25.203
What brings you here?

00:04:25.703 --> 00:04:28.414
You must've come all the way
from Engineering for a reason.

00:04:28.498 --> 00:04:32.627
Well, I wanted to speak to you
about this yesterday, but I forgot.

00:04:33.127 --> 00:04:34.253
Mun-oh,

00:04:34.837 --> 00:04:38.424
I heard you know the author Kim Su-hun.

00:04:41.719 --> 00:04:42.553
Who?

00:04:43.137 --> 00:04:43.971
Kim Su-hun?

00:04:44.055 --> 00:04:46.516
Yes. I heard you were classmates
back in university.

00:04:47.308 --> 00:04:50.728
I had no idea
you had such impressive connections.

00:04:50.812 --> 00:04:52.355
Had I known that from the start,

00:04:52.438 --> 00:04:54.941
I would have asked you
to introduce us earlier.

00:04:55.024 --> 00:04:56.109
What do you mean?

00:04:56.609 --> 00:04:59.821
I believe I told you
about this previously.

00:05:00.321 --> 00:05:04.617
I organize the School of Engineering's
monthly cultural events.

00:05:04.700 --> 00:05:07.662
Our students are emotionally stunted,
so I thought--

00:05:07.745 --> 00:05:08.955
Just get to the point.

00:05:09.038 --> 00:05:10.832
Right, yes. The point.

00:05:11.582 --> 00:05:15.336
The point is, we're in talks
to invite Kim Su-hun next month.

00:05:15.420 --> 00:05:19.799
To give a lecture on his new novel
and have a discussion afterward.

00:05:19.882 --> 00:05:23.177
I was hoping
you could host that discussion.

00:05:26.764 --> 00:05:27.598
Well?

00:05:30.852 --> 00:05:32.979
-You want me to host the discussion?
-Yes.

00:05:33.062 --> 00:05:35.648
Mr. Kim was the one
who suggested you first.

00:05:40.528 --> 00:05:42.363
Kim Su-hun suggested me?

00:05:42.447 --> 00:05:43.739
Yes.

00:05:44.323 --> 00:05:45.533
What did he say?

00:05:45.616 --> 00:05:49.203
Just that he would feel more at ease,
and it'd be fun to chat with a friend.

00:05:49.912 --> 00:05:51.539
He said he'd come if you did it.

00:05:57.712 --> 00:05:59.213
Kim Su-hun said that?

00:06:00.381 --> 00:06:01.215
Yes.

00:06:07.722 --> 00:06:10.433
-Road's slippery. Careful.
-Can we expect a great article?

00:06:10.516 --> 00:06:14.562
Don't worry, sir. Just be ready
to print more copies of the book.

00:06:14.645 --> 00:06:15.563
Su-hun.

00:06:19.609 --> 00:06:21.944
Mun-oh! Hey, just a second.

00:06:22.445 --> 00:06:23.404
Mr. Gu?

00:06:23.988 --> 00:06:26.616
Please go ahead. I'll be right there.

00:06:27.116 --> 00:06:30.244
-Okay, sure.
-Hurry. The real interview starts now.

00:06:30.328 --> 00:06:31.162
Right.

00:06:31.662 --> 00:06:33.915
-Join us at the pork rind joint.
-You got it.

00:06:36.501 --> 00:06:40.171
I should have given you a call first.
Sorry about that.

00:06:40.671 --> 00:06:44.383
Weren't we supposed to have
dinner together today?

00:06:45.176 --> 00:06:46.636
That's what I thought.

00:06:46.719 --> 00:06:48.763
Yeah, I was thinking the same.

00:06:49.514 --> 00:06:50.973
And I have something to say.

00:06:51.057 --> 00:06:54.101
But Mr. Gu suddenly decided to join us.

00:06:54.685 --> 00:06:55.770
You know Mr. Gu, right?

00:06:55.853 --> 00:06:58.564
Of course.
What writer doesn't know Gu Yeong-ho?

00:06:59.065 --> 00:07:00.691
First time seeing him in person.

00:07:02.902 --> 00:07:03.736
So,

00:07:04.946 --> 00:07:06.239
what did you have to say?

00:07:06.739 --> 00:07:07.823
What is it?

00:07:09.867 --> 00:07:13.037
Is it about what I asked you a while ago?

00:07:13.829 --> 00:07:14.664
That favor?

00:07:16.749 --> 00:07:17.625
Yeah.

00:07:20.586 --> 00:07:22.129
I don't think I can endorse you.

00:07:23.297 --> 00:07:26.217
I think I've been too liberal
with writing endorsements lately.

00:07:28.928 --> 00:07:31.013
Liberal?

00:07:32.598 --> 00:07:35.476
Did you even read my manuscript?

00:07:35.560 --> 00:07:36.936
Of course I did.

00:07:38.271 --> 00:07:40.648
But let's talk about that later, okay?

00:07:40.731 --> 00:07:41.774
No, hey, Su-hun.

00:07:42.567 --> 00:07:44.026
Tell me now.

00:07:44.527 --> 00:07:46.612
What did you think? Just tell me.

00:08:49.842 --> 00:08:53.846
I couldn't really tell
what the author was trying to say.

00:08:55.014 --> 00:08:56.724
It made me think,

00:08:57.224 --> 00:08:59.727
why bother writing
when you have nothing to say?

00:09:01.812 --> 00:09:03.814
It's okay to live as is.

00:09:05.316 --> 00:09:07.568
But, above all else,

00:09:08.611 --> 00:09:10.655
you should relearn sentence structures.

00:09:25.544 --> 00:09:27.838
<i>That's why</i>
<i>writing the first sentence is crucial.</i>

00:09:31.884 --> 00:09:33.761
The moment the first sentence is written,

00:09:34.345 --> 00:09:38.391
the author finally takes
their first step into their story.

00:09:42.061 --> 00:09:43.479
Listen to this sentence.

00:09:45.690 --> 00:09:50.528
"How happy I am that I am gone!"

00:09:52.863 --> 00:09:53.864
"My dear friend,

00:09:55.449 --> 00:09:57.993
what a thing is the heart of man!"

00:09:59.161 --> 00:10:01.372
Anyone know
which novel's first sentence this is?

00:10:05.626 --> 00:10:06.460
No one?

00:10:12.174 --> 00:10:15.636
This is the quintessential classic.
Goethe's--

00:10:19.682 --> 00:10:20.558
Who was that?

00:10:22.768 --> 00:10:23.978
What was that noise?

00:10:27.189 --> 00:10:28.357
Apologies.

00:10:35.364 --> 00:10:39.201
That was the first sentence of Goethe's
<i>The Sorrows of Young Werther</i>.

00:10:40.119 --> 00:10:41.245
As you all will know,

00:10:41.829 --> 00:10:45.958
it's written in the form of letters
sent by Werther to his friend Albert…

00:10:46.041 --> 00:10:47.710
Are my classes a joke to you?

00:10:52.006 --> 00:10:53.340
Am I a joke to you?

00:10:56.761 --> 00:10:57.595
Get up.

00:10:58.637 --> 00:10:59.889
Get up.

00:11:01.807 --> 00:11:02.725
You won't?

00:11:04.185 --> 00:11:05.311
Get out!

00:11:07.938 --> 00:11:09.023
Out of my class.

00:11:09.106 --> 00:11:12.193
It's not Albert, it's Wilhelm.

00:11:16.238 --> 00:11:17.156
What?

00:11:18.407 --> 00:11:20.785
Werther's friend is Wilhelm.

00:11:21.786 --> 00:11:26.332
Albert is the fiancé of Lotte,
the woman Werther loves.

00:11:30.920 --> 00:11:32.922
The object of Werther's jealousy,

00:11:33.756 --> 00:11:36.592
admiration, and inferiority complex.

00:11:38.093 --> 00:11:39.053
But,

00:11:40.805 --> 00:11:43.724
in the sense that all of those things
are part of friendship,

00:11:45.017 --> 00:11:47.269
I guess you could say they were friends.

00:11:48.854 --> 00:11:50.564
The object of his envy,

00:11:52.107 --> 00:11:53.400
and yet, his friend.

00:11:59.490 --> 00:12:02.368
Time's up, Professor.

00:12:08.040 --> 00:12:09.208
Class dismissed.

00:12:15.381 --> 00:12:16.465
Hey, get up.

00:12:33.148 --> 00:12:35.401
FUNDAMENTALS OF WRITING
CONCEPTS AND PRACTICES

00:12:35.484 --> 00:12:36.443
PROFESSOR HEO MUN-OH

00:12:36.527 --> 00:12:38.028
ELECTRONICS ENGINEERING
LEE KANG

00:12:38.112 --> 00:12:39.446
Hey, thank you.

00:12:39.947 --> 00:12:42.157
You saved me. I almost got cooked.

00:12:42.950 --> 00:12:45.035
I'll treat you to a nice meal today.

00:12:45.536 --> 00:12:46.412
What do you want?

00:12:46.912 --> 00:12:49.290
Whatever you want. Fried chicken, pizza…

00:12:49.957 --> 00:12:53.419
<i>But, if jealousy preceded any affection,</i>

00:12:53.919 --> 00:12:57.006
<i>could that relationship</i>
<i>still be called a friendship?</i>

00:13:00.634 --> 00:13:04.096
<i>I first met Se-yun in the winter</i>
<i>before we started school.</i>

00:13:04.179 --> 00:13:05.014
<i>A mere</i>

00:13:05.598 --> 00:13:06.599
<i>coincidence.</i>

00:13:14.607 --> 00:13:16.525
Hurry up and clear the table.

00:13:18.027 --> 00:13:19.445
Wait, this…

00:13:32.541 --> 00:13:33.959
I held onto this for you.

00:13:34.460 --> 00:13:36.253
Thank you.

00:13:37.880 --> 00:13:39.298
I found it.

00:13:57.733 --> 00:13:58.943
Thank you so much.

00:13:59.693 --> 00:14:00.819
Thank you.

00:14:03.656 --> 00:14:06.367
<i>Our meeting was a coincidence,</i>
<i>but us becoming friends</i>

00:14:07.076 --> 00:14:08.327
<i>wasn't a coincidence.</i>

00:14:09.119 --> 00:14:10.287
<i>I planned it.</i>

00:14:10.371 --> 00:14:11.497
CODING CLUB

00:14:19.505 --> 00:14:20.589
Are you in YDOC too?

00:14:21.090 --> 00:14:22.758
They gave these as freshmen goodies.

00:14:25.886 --> 00:14:28.847
I'm Kim Se-yun, class of '25.
Library and Information Science. You?

00:14:29.348 --> 00:14:31.600
Lee Kang, class of '25.
Electronics Engineering.

00:14:33.185 --> 00:14:34.895
An engineer taking this class?

00:14:34.979 --> 00:14:36.730
Then again, it is a required course.

00:14:40.859 --> 00:14:42.611
So do you know how to code?

00:14:43.112 --> 00:14:46.031
Honestly, I'm clueless.
I joined because I like video games.

00:14:50.119 --> 00:14:51.662
Coding isn't that hard.

00:14:52.454 --> 00:14:53.455
It's easy.

00:14:54.164 --> 00:14:54.999
Really?

00:14:58.460 --> 00:15:00.421
Wow, how do you do this?

00:15:01.255 --> 00:15:02.172
Teach me.

00:15:02.881 --> 00:15:05.467
Not now. I have to go to my part-time job.

00:15:07.553 --> 00:15:09.638
How about tomorrow?
Want to come to my place?

00:15:10.597 --> 00:15:12.307
<i>My plan worked.</i>

00:15:12.808 --> 00:15:14.018
-Your place?
-Yeah.

00:15:14.101 --> 00:15:16.270
<i>I finally became friends with Se-yun.</i>

00:15:16.770 --> 00:15:19.189
<i>Friendly enough to invite each other over.</i>

00:15:19.273 --> 00:15:20.983
TO BE CONTINUED..

00:16:10.407 --> 00:16:14.953
<i>Is it possible to feel nostalgia</i>
<i>for a place you've never been to?</i>

00:16:17.706 --> 00:16:20.084
<i>Is it possible to be filled with longing</i>

00:16:20.834 --> 00:16:22.836
<i>for someone you've never met?</i>

00:16:31.345 --> 00:16:33.889
<i>It was my first time at his house,</i>
<i>but it felt familiar.</i>

00:16:34.807 --> 00:16:37.101
<i>It looked just like it did in the photo.</i>

00:16:39.603 --> 00:16:41.063
Come this way.

00:16:45.984 --> 00:16:46.902
Mom.

00:16:49.655 --> 00:16:51.198
Oh, you're home.

00:16:51.698 --> 00:16:54.201
This is my friend from my university club.

00:16:55.244 --> 00:16:56.703
I mentioned him, didn't I?

00:16:58.455 --> 00:17:00.124
Right, it's you.

00:17:01.166 --> 00:17:02.501
Nice to meet you.

00:17:03.043 --> 00:17:03.919
I'm Lee Kang.

00:17:05.838 --> 00:17:07.422
<i>No, different from the photo.</i>

00:17:08.006 --> 00:17:10.217
<i>They were far more beautiful</i>
<i>than I'd expected.</i>

00:17:10.717 --> 00:17:11.552
<i>The house.</i>

00:17:11.635 --> 00:17:12.719
-So good.
-Right?

00:17:12.803 --> 00:17:13.637
<i>And the person.</i>

00:17:14.638 --> 00:17:16.265
I think I'm gifted.

00:17:16.348 --> 00:17:17.599
Good job.

00:17:18.350 --> 00:17:19.393
As you should.

00:17:54.803 --> 00:17:56.180
"To be continued.."

00:17:56.680 --> 00:17:59.766
Oh my. What is this? Who wrote this?

00:17:59.850 --> 00:18:00.851
Some kid.

00:18:02.019 --> 00:18:03.103
What do you think?

00:18:04.354 --> 00:18:05.647
I'm not sure.

00:18:07.191 --> 00:18:10.068
So he purposefully approached
and befriended this boy?

00:18:11.445 --> 00:18:12.529
No, that's not it.

00:18:13.030 --> 00:18:16.450
He pretended to be his friend
so he could go to his house?

00:18:16.533 --> 00:18:21.038
My goodness. What does this kid want?
Why would he write something like this?

00:18:21.121 --> 00:18:22.664
For God's sake.

00:18:22.748 --> 00:18:23.916
What the heck?

00:18:23.999 --> 00:18:27.753
I asked for your thoughts as an expert,
yet you're saying the same thing I did.

00:18:28.378 --> 00:18:30.547
What's he thinking? You're the therapist.

00:18:31.590 --> 00:18:34.426
Well, it's too early
to make any judgments based on this.

00:18:37.095 --> 00:18:39.640
His mental state doesn't seem so complex.

00:18:40.891 --> 00:18:41.767
He's envious.

00:18:42.726 --> 00:18:46.063
He must have seen something
he desperately wanted in that other kid.

00:18:46.146 --> 00:18:50.651
And since he can't do anything about it,
he's venting through writing. Imagination.

00:18:53.779 --> 00:18:55.656
While it's a bit peculiar,

00:18:55.739 --> 00:18:58.533
being able to express these feelings
is a good thing.

00:19:01.787 --> 00:19:03.580
I'm curious what he'll write next.

00:19:04.164 --> 00:19:05.582
He's a decent writer too.

00:19:07.209 --> 00:19:08.210
Isn't it a first

00:19:08.710 --> 00:19:10.337
for you to have such a student?

00:19:13.465 --> 00:19:14.549
Yes, it is.

00:19:15.842 --> 00:19:17.844
Are you going to take him under your wing?

00:19:18.345 --> 00:19:19.763
Don't be ridiculous.

00:19:20.264 --> 00:19:21.098
I'm going.

00:19:21.848 --> 00:19:23.100
Do you know…

00:19:26.895 --> 00:19:29.147
how long it's been
since you came into my room?

00:19:29.648 --> 00:19:30.482
Do you remember?

00:19:34.111 --> 00:19:35.112
Good night.

00:20:00.262 --> 00:20:02.472
<i>I'm curious what he'll write next.</i>

00:20:03.598 --> 00:20:06.143
<i>Isn't it a first for you</i>
<i>to have such a student?</i>

00:20:07.602 --> 00:20:09.646
<i>Are you going to take him under your wing?</i>

00:20:34.880 --> 00:20:36.757
Why did you ask me to stay behind?

00:20:37.966 --> 00:20:39.343
Did you have something

00:20:40.719 --> 00:20:41.636
to say?

00:20:44.181 --> 00:20:46.725
You humiliated me
in front of the class last time.

00:20:47.642 --> 00:20:48.769
Did it feel good?

00:21:05.827 --> 00:21:07.496
Is that Kim Se-yun?

00:21:09.915 --> 00:21:10.749
Yes.

00:21:11.833 --> 00:21:14.336
Does he know
what your assignment is about?

00:21:14.836 --> 00:21:16.004
Have you shown it to him?

00:21:17.297 --> 00:21:18.131
No.

00:21:19.007 --> 00:21:21.385
I thought only you
read the assignments, Professor.

00:21:22.219 --> 00:21:23.720
You said that in the first class.

00:21:28.767 --> 00:21:29.643
Sit.

00:21:48.453 --> 00:21:49.371
What is it…

00:21:51.498 --> 00:21:53.125
that you want to write about?

00:21:53.917 --> 00:21:55.293
What are you trying to write?

00:21:56.253 --> 00:21:57.295
What do you mean?

00:21:57.796 --> 00:22:00.674
It's an assignment,
so I just wrote whatever I felt like.

00:22:01.258 --> 00:22:02.092
As you told us to.

00:22:03.093 --> 00:22:04.428
No.

00:22:06.680 --> 00:22:09.516
You know what I'm asking you.

00:22:10.934 --> 00:22:12.269
Let's not play dumb.

00:22:22.946 --> 00:22:24.072
You…

00:22:27.033 --> 00:22:28.535
envy Kim Se-yun, don't you?

00:22:30.162 --> 00:22:31.788
And you want to be him?

00:22:33.457 --> 00:22:35.667
That's why you wrote this, isn't it?

00:22:40.839 --> 00:22:42.048
But you know,

00:22:43.633 --> 00:22:45.385
in Kim Se-yun's assignment,

00:22:45.927 --> 00:22:47.846
there's not a single word about you.

00:22:48.722 --> 00:22:50.807
He doesn't seem to care at all

00:22:50.891 --> 00:22:53.101
whether you envy him or not.

00:22:54.060 --> 00:22:55.729
You're the only one who's suffering.

00:23:00.317 --> 00:23:01.776
Do you know it too?

00:23:03.820 --> 00:23:04.905
That feeling?

00:23:15.499 --> 00:23:19.211
So are you suggesting
that I should write about something else?

00:23:21.171 --> 00:23:25.175
-There's nothing else I want to write.
-No, write. Write about this.

00:23:25.258 --> 00:23:28.428
My point is that you should keep writing.

00:23:28.512 --> 00:23:30.263
Even if it's hard, just write.

00:23:31.681 --> 00:23:33.725
What's important is wanting to write.

00:23:37.854 --> 00:23:38.939
You have talent.

00:23:43.735 --> 00:23:44.611
And

00:23:45.737 --> 00:23:48.573
take one-on-one literature lessons
from me. Once a week.

00:23:49.366 --> 00:23:50.659
-One-on-one?
-Yes.

00:23:50.742 --> 00:23:51.868
One-on-one.

00:23:54.287 --> 00:23:56.414
I'm saying I'll make time for you.

00:23:56.498 --> 00:23:57.791
What? Don't you get it?

00:23:57.874 --> 00:23:59.209
No, I don't think I can.

00:24:00.961 --> 00:24:02.587
I have several part-time jobs.

00:24:05.298 --> 00:24:07.008
And money matters more to me.

00:24:16.518 --> 00:24:17.394
Then,

00:24:18.812 --> 00:24:22.274
what if I pay you as much as you earn
from one of your part-time jobs?

00:24:30.240 --> 00:24:31.074
Why?

00:24:34.286 --> 00:24:35.161
Do you like me?

00:24:39.291 --> 00:24:41.668
Crazy bastard. You're talking nonsense.

00:24:50.302 --> 00:24:51.136
Lee Kang.

00:24:54.264 --> 00:24:57.809
Quit talking nonsense, you punk,
and listen to me carefully.

00:24:59.978 --> 00:25:02.272
<i>You can't be Kim Se-yun,</i>

00:25:02.814 --> 00:25:06.484
<i>but you can write as much as you want</i>
<i>about your desire to become him.</i>

00:25:07.944 --> 00:25:10.155
<i>As long as you can sublimate that feeling.</i>

00:25:10.822 --> 00:25:13.533
<i>That's what literature is.</i>
<i>That's the power of literature.</i>

00:25:16.620 --> 00:25:18.163
<i>I want to help you</i>

00:25:18.246 --> 00:25:22.000
<i>so that the things you write</i>
<i>don't end up as mere scribbles</i>

00:25:22.917 --> 00:25:24.628
<i>but become a coherent story.</i>

00:25:26.838 --> 00:25:27.672
<i>Because</i>

00:25:28.173 --> 00:25:30.300
talent is a rare thing,

00:25:30.967 --> 00:25:32.594
and I'm your teacher.

00:25:34.554 --> 00:25:38.016
<i>All right, Professor.</i>
<i>I'll quit one of my part-time jobs.</i>

00:25:44.356 --> 00:25:51.154
ALL RIGHT, TEACHER
I'LL QUIT ONE OF MY PART-TIME JOBS

00:26:32.195 --> 00:26:33.196
Why are you grinning?

00:26:34.447 --> 00:26:36.032
I just find it funny.

00:26:36.866 --> 00:26:40.161
Literature lessons?
I didn't think you'd actually do it.

00:26:41.871 --> 00:26:44.666
Anyway, it's nice to see you
in good spirits.

00:26:44.749 --> 00:26:47.627
Didn't you say you were running late
for your appointment?

00:26:48.128 --> 00:26:49.212
You should get going.

00:26:51.256 --> 00:26:53.883
Still, I don't quite like you
doing the lessons here.

00:26:53.967 --> 00:26:57.220
Why at home?
You could do them on campus or at a café.

00:26:58.388 --> 00:27:02.642
I told you, if we do them outside,
people will see us and start talking.

00:27:04.436 --> 00:27:08.314
And when you meet Professor Park
and Seong-hui, you can't tell them, okay?

00:27:08.815 --> 00:27:09.649
Say I was busy.

00:27:09.733 --> 00:27:13.278
Oh, all right. Why do you always
insist on being so secretive?

00:27:15.613 --> 00:27:17.407
I'm off. Enjoy your lesson.

00:27:17.490 --> 00:27:18.533
Sure.

00:28:17.509 --> 00:28:18.343
Hey.

00:28:20.011 --> 00:28:20.845
Come on in.

00:28:33.691 --> 00:28:34.567
This way.

00:28:42.534 --> 00:28:44.035
Why aren't you coming in?

00:28:55.797 --> 00:28:58.383
Why do you look so down?
You're here to study.

00:28:58.925 --> 00:29:00.885
You haven't even greeted me properly.

00:29:02.887 --> 00:29:04.097
I did say hi.

00:29:05.014 --> 00:29:06.766
You little… Sit.

00:29:09.185 --> 00:29:10.019
Actually…

00:29:13.189 --> 00:29:16.609
something's been weighing on me,
and I thought I'd tell you over the phone,

00:29:17.110 --> 00:29:19.821
but I figured I should tell you in person.

00:29:21.781 --> 00:29:22.866
What do you mean?

00:29:25.326 --> 00:29:26.953
I can't take these lessons.

00:29:29.455 --> 00:29:30.290
The thing is,

00:29:31.124 --> 00:29:33.751
something happened
when I was at Se-yun's place yesterday.

00:29:33.835 --> 00:29:37.422
I might not be able to go there again,
which means I won't be able to write.

00:29:37.964 --> 00:29:39.966
Then these classes would be pointless, so…

00:29:42.010 --> 00:29:42.844
Wait.

00:29:43.845 --> 00:29:46.723
Take your time and explain.
Why, what happened?

00:29:52.937 --> 00:29:55.315
Do you remember
I wrote about the coding club?

00:29:56.024 --> 00:29:56.858
Yeah.

00:29:57.567 --> 00:30:00.111
Our club has a competition
coming up in two weeks.

00:30:00.612 --> 00:30:03.031
The preliminaries
of a national tournament for clubs.

00:30:06.534 --> 00:30:09.078
Se-yun and I were going to enter
as a team,

00:30:09.579 --> 00:30:12.790
so I went over to his place yesterday
to study together, but…

00:30:13.374 --> 00:30:14.208
But?

00:30:15.043 --> 00:30:16.419
Try up to this page.

00:30:16.502 --> 00:30:17.337
Okay.

00:30:18.463 --> 00:30:21.090
-I'm going to the bathroom.
-Sure, go ahead.

00:30:57.543 --> 00:30:59.504
<i>I was only going to the bathroom,</i>

00:31:00.004 --> 00:31:01.798
<i>but I suddenly got curious.</i>

00:31:21.275 --> 00:31:24.237
<i>Frankly, it was wrong of me.</i>

00:32:54.243 --> 00:32:55.369
I'm sorry.

00:32:56.704 --> 00:32:58.414
I couldn't find the bathroom.

00:33:00.374 --> 00:33:03.795
I see. I thought you were my Yun.

00:33:03.878 --> 00:33:05.671
There's also a bathroom upstairs.

00:33:05.755 --> 00:33:07.924
And one for guests by the front door.

00:33:09.467 --> 00:33:11.302
Yes, understood.

00:33:12.136 --> 00:33:13.679
I'll use one of those from now on.

00:33:19.227 --> 00:33:22.522
<i>Even though I was out of line,</i>
<i>Se-yun's mom was kind.</i>

00:33:23.022 --> 00:33:25.817
<i>She didn't get mad,</i>
<i>was considerate and gracious,</i>

00:33:26.317 --> 00:33:28.277
<i>and didn't seem upset</i>
<i>during dinner, either.</i>

00:33:28.778 --> 00:33:30.613
-It's hot.
-Okay.

00:33:34.033 --> 00:33:35.785
What's taking you so long? Come on.

00:33:36.285 --> 00:33:38.204
The kids are hungry and waiting.

00:33:38.704 --> 00:33:40.289
Yes, be right there.

00:33:48.089 --> 00:33:52.927
So you're Se-yun's new friend.
Nice to meet you. Lee Kang, right?

00:33:54.178 --> 00:33:55.012
Hello.

00:33:55.096 --> 00:33:55.972
Have a seat.

00:33:59.976 --> 00:34:01.894
I hear you're great with computers.

00:34:02.728 --> 00:34:05.231
You're all Se-yun talks about these days.

00:34:06.315 --> 00:34:07.567
It's true.

00:34:08.526 --> 00:34:10.695
He's had so many friends
but never like this.

00:34:10.778 --> 00:34:12.697
I don't talk about him that much.

00:34:12.780 --> 00:34:16.993
The truth is, I'm only able to enter
this competition thanks to Kang.

00:34:17.493 --> 00:34:20.079
Even all the seniors
are floored by his skills.

00:34:21.122 --> 00:34:23.082
Hey, why are you exaggerating?

00:34:23.166 --> 00:34:24.041
Exaggerating?

00:34:24.625 --> 00:34:26.752
Anyway, please take good care of Se-yun.

00:34:27.253 --> 00:34:30.339
His dream is to become
a programmer now, all of a sudden.

00:34:31.424 --> 00:34:33.926
Had we known,
we'd have made him study engineering.

00:34:35.136 --> 00:34:36.345
Okay. Let's eat.

00:34:38.306 --> 00:34:39.307
Let's say grace first.

00:34:39.807 --> 00:34:42.977
In the name of the Father,
of the Son, and of the Holy Spirit. Amen.

00:34:43.060 --> 00:34:45.980
Bless us, O Lord, and these gifts,
which we are about to receive

00:34:46.063 --> 00:34:47.732
from thy bounty…

00:34:47.815 --> 00:34:51.277
<i>But, as I was about to head home,</i>
<i>I found out the truth.</i>

00:34:51.777 --> 00:34:53.446
<i>How she really felt about me.</i>

00:34:53.529 --> 00:34:57.283
I don't know. There's something
suspicious and sneaky about him.

00:34:57.950 --> 00:35:00.411
You know how everyone gives off a vibe.

00:35:00.912 --> 00:35:05.041
I felt it from the first time I met him.
I wish he'd stop coming over.

00:35:06.334 --> 00:35:07.376
What is it now?

00:35:09.837 --> 00:35:11.714
What's got you all worked up this time?

00:35:14.008 --> 00:35:16.719
We can't exactly ban a friend
who Se-yun likes.

00:35:17.220 --> 00:35:19.222
All we can do is just watch over him.

00:35:20.473 --> 00:35:23.768
Do you know what happened earlier today?
He was in our bedroom…

00:35:25.811 --> 00:35:30.358
I'm just saying I'd prefer our Yun
to be friends with someone

00:35:30.900 --> 00:35:32.652
more cheerful and lively.

00:35:33.402 --> 00:35:34.570
Seriously?

00:35:35.655 --> 00:35:38.199
I thought the kid was fine. Seemed smart.

00:35:39.075 --> 00:35:43.037
Well then, let's at least leave them be
until after the competition.

00:35:43.788 --> 00:35:45.206
What if they win an award?

00:35:46.582 --> 00:35:50.795
They say awards at competitions like that
stand out on job applications.

00:35:51.295 --> 00:35:53.714
That's been on my mind too.

00:35:54.507 --> 00:35:55.591
All right.

00:35:56.092 --> 00:35:58.427
If it means it's going to help our son.

00:35:59.178 --> 00:36:01.597
-Let's revisit this after the competition.
-Yeah.

00:36:13.776 --> 00:36:15.945
What'd you do that for, huh?

00:36:16.028 --> 00:36:17.863
I know what I did was wrong.

00:36:20.199 --> 00:36:22.910
So, are you telling me

00:36:24.328 --> 00:36:27.665
that you have to win that competition
or whatever it's called

00:36:28.165 --> 00:36:30.376
in order to keep going over to his place?

00:36:30.960 --> 00:36:32.920
Yes. That's how it is.

00:36:33.504 --> 00:36:36.757
Then win it. Just do it.
You're good at programming, aren't you?

00:36:37.258 --> 00:36:38.968
Don't talk about what you don't know.

00:36:39.051 --> 00:36:41.554
I may be better than Se-yun,
but I don't stand a chance.

00:36:46.600 --> 00:36:47.893
Hey, but it's not like

00:36:48.436 --> 00:36:51.522
you have to go inside that house
in order to be able to write.

00:36:53.607 --> 00:36:56.402
What would I feel or write about
if I don't?

00:36:56.485 --> 00:36:57.695
That was my inspiration.

00:36:59.739 --> 00:37:00.740
You're right.

00:37:01.449 --> 00:37:02.575
Yes, that's true.

00:37:03.743 --> 00:37:04.577
That's true.

00:37:07.246 --> 00:37:08.622
Then what should we do?

00:37:09.206 --> 00:37:12.918
We need to come up with a good idea…

00:37:14.837 --> 00:37:17.089
There might be a way, but…

00:37:19.216 --> 00:37:20.051
What is it?

00:37:28.893 --> 00:37:31.854
Forget it. You couldn't do it, Mr. Heo.

00:37:32.355 --> 00:37:35.775
What are you talking about, punk?
What couldn't I do? Tell me.

00:37:43.991 --> 00:37:45.159
The competition problems.

00:37:46.702 --> 00:37:47.828
Competition problems?

00:37:51.290 --> 00:37:52.416
What about them?

00:38:07.473 --> 00:38:08.557
You don't mean…

00:38:11.519 --> 00:38:13.479
You're not asking me…

00:38:15.272 --> 00:38:16.732
to steal the competition problems…

00:38:19.026 --> 00:38:20.069
are you?

00:38:21.862 --> 00:38:24.156
I can't think of any other way
out of this.

00:38:29.412 --> 00:38:30.538
Are you crazy?

00:38:33.040 --> 00:38:34.333
You're a lunatic.

00:38:38.838 --> 00:38:39.922
You little punk.

00:38:41.549 --> 00:38:44.844
I'm your teacher
and a professor at that school!

00:38:45.511 --> 00:38:47.805
How dare you ask such a thing!

00:38:52.268 --> 00:38:53.686
Hey, get out.

00:38:54.728 --> 00:38:57.857
Get out of here! I'm not interested
in giving you lessons anymore.

00:38:58.441 --> 00:39:00.568
You're a real piece of work, aren't you?

00:39:02.445 --> 00:39:03.529
Get out!

00:39:07.908 --> 00:39:09.368
Then it can't be helped.

00:39:11.162 --> 00:39:13.122
I'll just forget about
your teaching offer.

00:39:22.256 --> 00:39:23.674
Why, that punk…

00:39:25.468 --> 00:39:27.636
What the hell is wrong with him?

00:39:40.524 --> 00:39:42.568
Why didn't you hand in your assignment?

00:39:43.319 --> 00:39:45.029
I had nothing to write about.

00:39:53.412 --> 00:39:54.288
Hey, Lee Kang!

00:39:55.498 --> 00:39:59.418
Are you really not handing something in?
At this rate, I won't help you…

00:40:02.004 --> 00:40:02.838
Hey.

00:40:04.507 --> 00:40:05.382
Hey!

00:40:05.466 --> 00:40:06.967
ELECTRONICS ENGINEERING
LEE KANG

00:40:23.817 --> 00:40:27.821
GUEST LECTURE WITH AUTHOR KIM SU-HUN

00:40:29.156 --> 00:40:31.075
AUTHOR OF EYES OF THE HOUSE

00:41:08.904 --> 00:41:09.947
Hey, Professor Park.

00:41:10.447 --> 00:41:12.032
<i>Hey, Mun-oh! I mean…</i>

00:41:12.533 --> 00:41:14.785
<i>Professor Heo, where are you?</i>

00:41:15.452 --> 00:41:16.412
Well…

00:41:16.495 --> 00:41:19.081
<i>Mr. Kim is already here waiting for you.</i>

00:41:19.582 --> 00:41:22.209
<i>You should have a chat over coffee</i>
<i>before the lecture.</i>

00:41:22.293 --> 00:41:23.460
Is that so?

00:41:23.544 --> 00:41:26.714
Deary me.
You see, I'm on my way right now.

00:41:27.214 --> 00:41:30.259
About ten minutes?
I think I'll be there in about ten.

00:41:30.342 --> 00:41:34.805
Tell him to have a cup of tea
and wait a little longer, yeah?

00:41:35.306 --> 00:41:37.725
Sorry about that. I'll be there soon.

00:41:38.684 --> 00:41:39.977
Okay, see you soon.

00:41:52.239 --> 00:41:54.033
Wow, long time no see.

00:41:54.908 --> 00:41:57.911
-It's been a while.
-It has indeed. Been a while.

00:41:57.995 --> 00:42:00.122
When was the last time we saw each other?

00:42:00.205 --> 00:42:02.166
Life's so busy. I can't remember…

00:42:02.666 --> 00:42:03.709
Let me see.

00:42:03.792 --> 00:42:06.962
When was it? I can't quite remember.

00:42:08.422 --> 00:42:11.133
I guess it really is nice
meeting old friends.

00:42:11.216 --> 00:42:14.428
Why, I've never seen Professor Heo
with such a big smile.

00:42:14.511 --> 00:42:15.888
Is that so?

00:42:17.431 --> 00:42:20.476
Yeah, I'm happy too. It's good to see you.

00:42:22.061 --> 00:42:23.270
You haven't changed.

00:42:24.146 --> 00:42:28.609
Over seven full-length novels
and four short story collections,

00:42:28.692 --> 00:42:30.486
you've delved deep

00:42:31.278 --> 00:42:34.740
into the complexity of the human psyche.

00:42:34.823 --> 00:42:37.701
But in your latest work,
<i>Eyes of the House</i>,

00:42:37.785 --> 00:42:39.745
you've taken an entirely new approach

00:42:40.245 --> 00:42:43.082
by incorporating the techniques
of mystery novels.

00:42:43.165 --> 00:42:43.999
That's right.

00:42:44.833 --> 00:42:47.002
I borrowed from the mystery genre.

00:42:47.628 --> 00:42:49.672
But while your standard mystery novel

00:42:50.172 --> 00:42:54.551
focuses on solving the case,
I was interested in something different.

00:42:55.052 --> 00:42:59.473
I broke every scene down into fragments,
including the murder scene,

00:42:59.556 --> 00:43:03.102
and scrambled them so it's difficult
to tell the sequence of events.

00:43:04.520 --> 00:43:08.357
Because what was important to me
wasn't who the culprit was,

00:43:08.857 --> 00:43:10.901
nor the resolution
and conclusion of the case.

00:43:10.984 --> 00:43:15.280
It was the multi-layered
human relationships surrounding it.

00:43:17.991 --> 00:43:19.118
You all got that, right?

00:43:20.536 --> 00:43:21.620
Well, I understood.

00:43:23.747 --> 00:43:26.625
Yes, it's truly remarkable.

00:43:26.709 --> 00:43:28.419
That's why most readers

00:43:29.128 --> 00:43:32.297
have reviewed this book
as "very novel" and "refreshing."

00:43:33.716 --> 00:43:36.385
But…

00:43:38.011 --> 00:43:39.096
But

00:43:40.431 --> 00:43:41.640
some people…

00:43:45.310 --> 00:43:46.145
Some people?

00:43:47.938 --> 00:43:52.359
Well, some people say… Put differently…

00:43:54.319 --> 00:43:58.657
This may be a little uncomfortable
for you to hear,

00:43:59.158 --> 00:44:02.703
but since this is a place
for free discussion,

00:44:02.786 --> 00:44:04.037
I'll say it.

00:44:06.790 --> 00:44:09.710
"With this novel,
Kim Su-hun is catering to the masses."

00:44:10.210 --> 00:44:15.090
Well, the fact is that there are some
who hold critical opinions like this.

00:44:18.385 --> 00:44:22.097
Of course, this isn't my personal opinion.

00:44:22.181 --> 00:44:24.767
Before I came to this lecture hall today,

00:44:24.850 --> 00:44:28.312
I received a few questions
from some students.

00:44:28.937 --> 00:44:30.898
This was one of the questions.

00:44:32.357 --> 00:44:33.609
Just a moment.

00:44:33.692 --> 00:44:35.277
So…

00:44:36.361 --> 00:44:39.490
Let's see.

00:44:39.573 --> 00:44:41.825
Where is it? Oh, here it is.

00:44:42.367 --> 00:44:43.744
So,

00:44:44.912 --> 00:44:47.122
this was the student's question.

00:44:48.207 --> 00:44:49.875
"Mr. Kim Su-hun,

00:44:49.958 --> 00:44:53.921
you've long established
a reputation in literary fiction,

00:44:54.004 --> 00:44:59.092
so I had great respect for you
and was a huge fan of yours."

00:44:59.760 --> 00:45:05.057
"But I was quite disappointed when you
suddenly came out with a mystery novel."

00:45:05.557 --> 00:45:09.353
"Is it perhaps because you don't have
any stories of your own left to tell

00:45:09.853 --> 00:45:14.233
that you had no choice
but to cater to the masses?"

00:45:14.983 --> 00:45:16.610
That's pretty harsh.

00:45:17.569 --> 00:45:19.905
"If you don't have
any stories left to tell…

00:45:21.907 --> 00:45:22.991
wouldn't it be better

00:45:23.784 --> 00:45:28.163
to stop writing altogether?"

00:45:29.081 --> 00:45:30.207
Something like that.

00:45:31.583 --> 00:45:33.335
Which student asked this question?

00:45:41.927 --> 00:45:44.221
Is this, by any chance,
your opinion, Professor Heo?

00:45:44.847 --> 00:45:46.974
What? No, it's…

00:45:47.641 --> 00:45:49.184
I'm just messing with you.

00:45:49.810 --> 00:45:52.563
I'd like to thank the fan who asked this,
whoever you are.

00:45:52.646 --> 00:45:57.109
Sounds like you're very interested in me
and have followed my work for a long time.

00:45:57.609 --> 00:45:59.194
To answer your question,

00:45:59.820 --> 00:46:02.114
yes, you're right. Catering to the masses.

00:46:03.866 --> 00:46:06.743
The verb "to cater to"
could be interpreted two ways.

00:46:06.827 --> 00:46:10.831
"To satisfy the desires or needs
of the general public."

00:46:11.415 --> 00:46:13.625
That can be interpreted negatively
as pandering,

00:46:13.709 --> 00:46:15.210
but it could be a positive.

00:46:15.961 --> 00:46:17.462
"Finding common ground."

00:46:17.963 --> 00:46:20.674
According to that second definition,

00:46:21.174 --> 00:46:23.051
it is essential to cater to all in art.

00:46:23.594 --> 00:46:26.930
What could be more exciting
than the author and the readers

00:46:27.014 --> 00:46:29.391
finding common ground?

00:46:31.143 --> 00:46:34.730
What truly matters is not "what"
but always "how."

00:46:35.314 --> 00:46:38.066
A flexible and multi-faceted
perspective is crucial.

00:46:39.026 --> 00:46:41.695
If you insist on sticking to
a world you're familiar with,

00:46:41.778 --> 00:46:43.864
your creativity will inevitably wither.

00:46:44.740 --> 00:46:48.535
That is why I will continue to tell
new stories, experiment with new forms,

00:46:48.619 --> 00:46:52.372
and strive to become even better
at catering to the masses.

00:47:05.302 --> 00:47:07.638
The atmosphere was great today, wasn't it?

00:47:07.721 --> 00:47:10.682
-The students' response was just…
-It was amazing.

00:47:10.766 --> 00:47:11.934
-Mr. Kim.
-Thanks.

00:47:12.434 --> 00:47:16.355
Of all the events we've organized so far,
today's had the highest attendance.

00:47:16.438 --> 00:47:18.815
The dean was so excited.

00:47:19.566 --> 00:47:21.902
Thanks to you,
I got a lot of compliments today.

00:47:21.985 --> 00:47:27.074
Oh, please. It's all thanks to you
and Professor Heo, who hosted.

00:47:27.950 --> 00:47:31.536
But more than anything,
the students were listening so intently,

00:47:31.620 --> 00:47:33.997
I got very excited
and talked way more than usual.

00:47:34.081 --> 00:47:37.000
-Thank you.
-The students really were great today.

00:47:37.084 --> 00:47:39.169
Why don't they act like that
in my lectures?

00:47:39.670 --> 00:47:41.088
You just have to do better.

00:47:41.171 --> 00:47:43.131
Let's have a drink. It's an honor.

00:47:43.215 --> 00:47:44.049
Yes.

00:47:44.132 --> 00:47:46.134
-Lovely to meet you.
-Truly an honor.

00:47:53.934 --> 00:47:56.895
Why have you been so quiet, Professor Heo?

00:47:57.854 --> 00:48:01.692
Not at all. I've just been listening
and enjoying your conversation.

00:48:01.775 --> 00:48:03.819
Right. You two are friends, aren't you?

00:48:03.902 --> 00:48:05.487
Yes, from university.

00:48:07.406 --> 00:48:08.657
Do you enjoy teaching?

00:48:10.450 --> 00:48:12.327
How could it possibly be fun?

00:48:13.412 --> 00:48:19.001
Mr. Kim, your daughter's pen name
is Lee I-pil, isn't it?

00:48:19.084 --> 00:48:22.337
She made her debut last year
with <i>Seventeen Green Wings</i>.

00:48:22.421 --> 00:48:23.797
Wow, really?

00:48:23.880 --> 00:48:26.842
That writer who made a clean sweep
of the literary debut awards

00:48:26.925 --> 00:48:29.177
was your daughter? Wow.

00:48:29.261 --> 00:48:30.929
I think I've heard about it too.

00:48:31.013 --> 00:48:34.016
I guess there are no secrets
in this world.

00:48:34.099 --> 00:48:37.185
I even came up with her pen name
so people wouldn't know.

00:48:37.269 --> 00:48:39.771
Wow, how impressive.

00:48:39.855 --> 00:48:42.232
I guess literary talent
runs in the family.

00:48:42.315 --> 00:48:44.609
You must be so proud. I'm so jealous.

00:48:45.485 --> 00:48:50.323
A talented child <i>and </i>your career?
You really do have it all.

00:49:47.380 --> 00:49:48.381
Mr. Heo.

00:49:49.925 --> 00:49:51.009
What are you…

00:49:55.055 --> 00:49:55.972
You work here?

00:49:56.723 --> 00:49:57.557
Yes.

00:49:59.142 --> 00:50:00.936
You must be here with someone.

00:50:01.937 --> 00:50:02.896
Yeah.

00:50:04.439 --> 00:50:06.608
What were you scribbling while working?

00:50:11.696 --> 00:50:12.572
This is just…

00:50:13.657 --> 00:50:16.535
Just what, punk?
You don't even turn in your assignments.

00:50:20.413 --> 00:50:21.790
Actually, I was thinking…

00:50:24.084 --> 00:50:26.086
of applying to a writing contest.

00:50:26.711 --> 00:50:28.380
Literary debut awards.

00:50:29.256 --> 00:50:32.425
I heard the prize money can be decent,
so I thought I'd give it a shot.

00:50:33.009 --> 00:50:34.427
What, a contest?

00:50:35.345 --> 00:50:36.930
Mr. Heo, you told me

00:50:38.348 --> 00:50:39.516
that I have talent.

00:50:41.935 --> 00:50:45.605
<i>But I haven't found a story</i>
<i>that I want to write just yet.</i>

00:51:03.748 --> 00:51:05.834
Literary debut awards.

00:51:10.213 --> 00:51:11.840
That rascal.

00:51:16.052 --> 00:51:18.096
What a load of crap.

00:51:25.896 --> 00:51:27.314
LITERARY DEBUT AWARD
LEE KANG

00:51:28.523 --> 00:51:30.942
Thank you. Thank you so much.

00:51:33.612 --> 00:51:36.865
But this award truly belongs

00:51:37.532 --> 00:51:38.825
to someone else.

00:51:38.909 --> 00:51:40.577
"You have talent."

00:51:41.077 --> 00:51:43.622
The person who opened my eyes
with those words.

00:51:44.456 --> 00:51:45.916
The person who taught me

00:51:46.416 --> 00:51:49.586
what literature is,
and beyond that, what it means to live.

00:51:53.548 --> 00:51:54.799
My mentor, Mr. Heo Mun-oh.

00:51:58.053 --> 00:51:59.596
Thank you so much.

00:53:00.991 --> 00:53:02.033
Hey.

00:53:03.660 --> 00:53:07.414
Do you think the literary debut awards
are child's play?

00:53:09.124 --> 00:53:11.751
You don't stand a chance
with your skills, you punk.

00:53:24.973 --> 00:53:25.974
Then…

00:53:28.768 --> 00:53:31.354
If you have them,

00:53:31.438 --> 00:53:34.983
the problems
for that competition or whatever…

00:53:38.820 --> 00:53:41.573
will you start taking writing seriously?

00:53:44.284 --> 00:53:46.202
And take the literature lessons again?

00:53:58.923 --> 00:53:59.758
Then, kid,

00:54:00.508 --> 00:54:03.553
what do I need to do? Tell me!

00:54:15.315 --> 00:54:17.067
Are you sure you're okay with this?

00:54:18.401 --> 00:54:21.488
<i>It's actually pretty simple.</i>
<i>You just need to do as I say.</i>

00:54:21.988 --> 00:54:24.032
<i>Yeah, well, what do I need to do exactly?</i>

00:54:24.115 --> 00:54:26.451
<i>Go to Professor Park Hyeong-jong's office.</i>

00:54:27.118 --> 00:54:28.203
<i>Park Hyeong-jong?</i>

00:54:28.953 --> 00:54:30.872
<i>-Professor Park from Engineering?</i>
<i>-Yes.</i>

00:54:30.955 --> 00:54:33.875
<i>He's head of the competition's</i>
<i>problem selection committee.</i>

00:54:35.085 --> 00:54:37.545
<i>That guy just needs to have</i>
<i>his fingers in every pie.</i>

00:54:38.129 --> 00:54:41.800
<i>Wait. How did you know</i>
<i>that I'm acquainted with Professor Park?</i>

00:54:42.384 --> 00:54:44.552
<i>Do you think I'd have asked otherwise?</i>

00:54:44.636 --> 00:54:46.554
<i>I've seen you two talking before.</i>

00:54:47.055 --> 00:54:48.264
-Enjoy your meal.
-Yeah.

00:54:48.348 --> 00:54:49.349
Eat up.

00:54:49.974 --> 00:54:51.851
-Here you are.
-Thank you.

00:54:55.480 --> 00:54:57.649
-Enjoy your meal.
-You too.

00:55:01.444 --> 00:55:02.404
Professor Park.

00:55:03.571 --> 00:55:05.365
Mun-oh! Come join me.

00:55:06.116 --> 00:55:08.076
-You're eating quite late.
-As are you.

00:55:08.159 --> 00:55:11.621
<i>And after I'm in Professor Park's office?</i>
<i>What do I do once I'm there?</i>

00:55:11.704 --> 00:55:12.539
This is nice.

00:55:12.622 --> 00:55:16.876
<i>The competition is tomorrow,</i>
<i>so the problems will be on his computer.</i>

00:55:16.960 --> 00:55:20.004
<i>All you need to do is copy them</i>
<i>onto a USB drive. Simple, right?</i>

00:55:20.088 --> 00:55:23.425
<i>Punk, you call that simple?</i>
<i>How would I get into his computer?</i>

00:55:23.925 --> 00:55:25.593
<i>I'd need to know his password!</i>

00:55:25.677 --> 00:55:30.014
<i>Right, that's why Professor Park</i>
<i>needs to unlock it himself.</i>

00:55:33.601 --> 00:55:34.436
Professor Park.

00:55:36.813 --> 00:55:40.275
I have a favor to ask.

00:55:40.900 --> 00:55:43.653
Wow, you've never asked
for a favor before.

00:55:44.821 --> 00:55:45.905
Go ahead.

00:55:45.989 --> 00:55:47.574
It's just that

00:55:47.657 --> 00:55:52.454
I was thinking it's about time
I updated the way I take attendance.

00:55:52.537 --> 00:55:53.663
-Really?
-Yes.

00:55:53.746 --> 00:55:56.166
You told me about it once before.

00:55:56.249 --> 00:55:58.626
Wow, this is music to my ears.

00:55:59.127 --> 00:56:01.546
Yeah, it's about time you updated it.

00:56:01.629 --> 00:56:04.966
Okay, I'll go to your office tomorrow
and install it for you.

00:56:05.049 --> 00:56:06.509
No, not my office.

00:56:07.427 --> 00:56:10.263
I'd like to do it at your office.

00:56:10.346 --> 00:56:15.310
Shouldn't I at least see
how it's run first?

00:56:17.103 --> 00:56:17.937
Really?

00:56:18.021 --> 00:56:21.649
I don't really have time today,
so come to my office tomorrow.

00:56:21.733 --> 00:56:23.318
-I'll show you.
-Tomorrow?

00:56:23.818 --> 00:56:26.279
No, tomorrow's too late.
It has to be done today.

00:56:28.239 --> 00:56:32.494
I have something to attend to tomorrow,
so I'll be a bit busy.

00:56:33.369 --> 00:56:36.039
Can't I just stop by for a bit today?

00:56:36.623 --> 00:56:38.958
-Today? Now?
-Yeah, it won't take long.

00:56:39.542 --> 00:56:41.878
Okay, well, I have a little time to spare.

00:56:41.961 --> 00:56:44.839
-Let's go, then.
-Okay. Let's swing by now, then.

00:56:44.923 --> 00:56:47.008
-Strike while the iron is hot.
-Now?

00:56:47.091 --> 00:56:49.302
Yeah, just for a bit.
This food is terrible.

00:56:49.385 --> 00:56:50.512
I barely ate anything.

00:56:50.595 --> 00:56:53.348
It's terrible.
I'll treat you to some duck later.

00:56:53.431 --> 00:56:54.265
But…

00:56:54.766 --> 00:56:56.184
-Let's go, okay?
-But this food…

00:56:56.267 --> 00:56:57.560
-Come on.
-TA Kim.

00:56:57.644 --> 00:56:59.020
-Yes?
-Our trays, please.

00:56:59.103 --> 00:57:00.146
-Sure.
-Sorry.

00:57:00.230 --> 00:57:01.731
-Sorry.
-Goodbye.

00:57:01.814 --> 00:57:03.983
I blathered on
for about 30 minutes, I think?

00:57:04.067 --> 00:57:07.570
But when the show aired,
I was only on for about a minute or two.

00:57:08.071 --> 00:57:12.534
And after coming all the way to my office
and begging me to do it.

00:57:14.118 --> 00:57:15.870
It's truly convenient.

00:57:16.371 --> 00:57:18.122
-Hello.
-Hi, Mi-jin.

00:57:18.665 --> 00:57:20.250
<i>No, I can't do it.</i>

00:57:20.333 --> 00:57:22.377
<i>I just don't think I can do it.</i>

00:57:22.460 --> 00:57:25.588
<i>How could I, an educator, do such a thing?</i>

00:57:25.672 --> 00:57:27.590
<i>It's too late to say that now.</i>

00:57:30.260 --> 00:57:32.220
Mun-oh, are you feeling unwell?

00:57:34.013 --> 00:57:36.057
Professor Park.

00:57:36.724 --> 00:57:39.769
I'm sorry, but I need to go
to the bathroom quickly.

00:57:40.311 --> 00:57:42.564
All right. Be back soon.

00:57:42.647 --> 00:57:43.773
-Okay.
-I'll be inside.

00:57:43.856 --> 00:57:45.108
Yeah, sorry about that.

00:57:59.914 --> 00:58:01.749
<i>There's no need to feel guilty.</i>

00:58:02.250 --> 00:58:04.711
<i>I'm not going to participate</i>
<i>in the finals anyway,</i>

00:58:04.794 --> 00:58:07.171
<i>so we wouldn't be hurting anybody.</i>

00:58:13.511 --> 00:58:17.098
Hit this,
and I'll log in with my account first.

00:58:17.849 --> 00:58:19.183
Once you're logged in…

00:58:20.059 --> 00:58:21.394
<i>The problem is,</i>

00:58:21.894 --> 00:58:24.355
<i>I'm not sure how we could get him</i>

00:58:24.439 --> 00:58:25.523
<i>out of his office.</i>

00:58:25.607 --> 00:58:26.649
<i>For that,</i>

00:58:27.650 --> 00:58:28.943
<i>I've come up with a plan.</i>

00:58:29.027 --> 00:58:29.861
<i>What?</i>

00:58:30.361 --> 00:58:32.030
<i>You have? What is it?</i>

00:58:32.113 --> 00:58:36.367
…the attendance scores
will automatically be added to the final…

00:58:37.619 --> 00:58:39.579
-What's wrong?
-My chest.

00:58:40.079 --> 00:58:42.999
-It's coming.
-Mun-oh, what's wrong?

00:58:43.625 --> 00:58:44.917
I feel it coming.

00:58:45.001 --> 00:58:45.835
What…

00:58:46.336 --> 00:58:48.087
Are you okay? Should I call 911?

00:58:48.171 --> 00:58:50.882
No, you don't have to call them.

00:58:50.965 --> 00:58:52.759
-But…
-Just give me a minute.

00:58:54.218 --> 00:58:55.261
What is it?

00:58:55.345 --> 00:58:57.639
My meds must be in my car.

00:58:58.139 --> 00:58:59.891
Hey, what meds?

00:58:59.974 --> 00:59:01.184
For my angina.

00:59:01.768 --> 00:59:03.645
Mun-oh, you have angina?

00:59:03.728 --> 00:59:05.396
Okay, just wait here a minute.

00:59:05.480 --> 00:59:06.397
I'm so sorry.

00:59:06.481 --> 00:59:08.191
-Just wait here.
-I'm sorry.

00:59:08.274 --> 00:59:09.233
I'll be right back!

00:59:10.026 --> 00:59:11.736
-Hello, Professor.
-Hey, yeah.

00:59:25.625 --> 00:59:28.002
<i>-What medicine is it?</i>
<i>-You don't need to know, punk.</i>

00:59:29.587 --> 00:59:30.672
<i>It's for hemorrhoids.</i>

00:59:36.302 --> 00:59:37.595
Oh man, come on.

00:59:37.679 --> 00:59:38.763
Damn it!

00:59:40.348 --> 00:59:44.560
<i>But the parking lot is too close.</i>
<i>It won't take him more than five minutes.</i>

00:59:44.644 --> 00:59:46.020
<i>Five minutes is plenty.</i>

00:59:46.521 --> 00:59:47.897
<i>Just tell me the file name.</i>

00:59:48.898 --> 00:59:52.110
<i>The thing is, I don't know</i>
<i>what the file name would be.</i>

00:59:52.193 --> 00:59:53.027
<i>What?</i>

00:59:53.778 --> 00:59:55.238
<i>You damn punk!</i>

01:00:13.214 --> 01:00:15.675
<i>You're going to end up making me ill.</i>

01:00:20.304 --> 01:00:21.723
Damn it, where is it?

01:00:24.851 --> 01:00:25.810
Let's see.

01:00:39.449 --> 01:00:40.867
Oh, here it is!

01:00:40.950 --> 01:00:43.035
YEONSEO UNIVERSITY
PROGRAMMING COMPETITION

01:00:43.119 --> 01:00:44.370
ANSWERS
COMPETITION PROBLEMS

01:00:44.871 --> 01:00:46.247
-Hello.
-Yeah.

01:00:48.499 --> 01:00:50.001
Hey, yeah.

01:01:10.938 --> 01:01:11.939
Got it.

01:01:12.690 --> 01:01:13.649
It's done.

01:01:19.238 --> 01:01:20.448
Damn it.

01:01:24.577 --> 01:01:26.454
Why is it so slow?

01:01:28.122 --> 01:01:29.248
50%.

01:01:30.541 --> 01:01:32.293
Come on, hurry.

01:01:35.922 --> 01:01:37.882
Okay. Almost there.

01:01:37.965 --> 01:01:39.717
Hurry.

01:01:44.222 --> 01:01:45.681
Just a little more.

01:01:52.063 --> 01:01:53.356
Mun-oh, your meds.

01:01:53.940 --> 01:01:54.899
Right.

01:01:54.982 --> 01:01:55.900
Are you okay?

01:01:58.194 --> 01:02:00.112
-Are you okay?
-Thanks, Professor Park.

01:02:00.196 --> 01:02:02.740
I feel much better, thanks to you.

01:02:02.824 --> 01:02:05.952
You see, it just swoops in.

01:02:06.035 --> 01:02:08.287
-Yes?
-Then it flies away.

01:02:09.413 --> 01:02:10.498
Sorry for the bother.

01:02:10.581 --> 01:02:11.415
No, it's…

01:02:11.499 --> 01:02:13.251
Oh, and Professor Park.

01:02:13.334 --> 01:02:16.087
I thought about it,

01:02:16.170 --> 01:02:18.673
and maybe my way is better after all.

01:02:19.173 --> 01:02:20.007
Sorry?

01:02:20.091 --> 01:02:21.676
-Thanks anyway.
-Yeah.

01:02:22.176 --> 01:02:23.636
-Are you sure you're okay?
-Yeah.

01:02:24.804 --> 01:02:26.305
But how are you suddenly fine?

01:02:32.019 --> 01:02:33.396
Sheesh, that scared me.

01:02:35.314 --> 01:02:36.190
Damn.

01:02:36.816 --> 01:02:37.650
I'm beat.

01:02:48.661 --> 01:02:50.788
-Hello, Professor.
-Yeah.

01:03:09.682 --> 01:03:10.683
Hello.

01:03:10.766 --> 01:03:12.435
Hello, Professor.

01:03:21.444 --> 01:03:23.571
Professor! Hello.

01:05:01.585 --> 01:05:03.462
Mun-oh. Heo Mun-oh.

01:05:03.963 --> 01:05:05.339
You've lost it.

01:05:05.840 --> 01:05:07.133
Totally lost the plot.

01:05:12.847 --> 01:05:16.225
Mun-oh, what are you even doing?

01:05:17.643 --> 01:05:20.604
NOTES FROM THE LAST ROW

01:07:46.750 --> 01:07:51.755
Subtitle translation by: Jimin Choi